NJ Blogs: Community Code of Conduct
​1. Our Pledge
​We are committed to providing a friendly, safe, and welcoming environment for all users of the NJ Blogs platform, regardless of level of experience, gender identity and expression, sexual orientation, disability, personal appearance, race, ethnicity, age, religion, or nationality.
​2. Expected Behavior
​Be Respectful: Treat others with kindness. Disagreeing is fine, but do so constructively and without personal attacks.
​Share Knowledge: As a blogging platform, we encourage mentorship and the sharing of ideas to help others grow.
​Collaborate Openly: Support fellow developers and writers in their journey.
​Focus on the Tech: Keep discussions and content centered around the goals of the hackathon and the purpose of the platform.
​3. Unacceptable Behavior
​The following behaviors are considered harassment and are strictly prohibited:
​Violence, threats of violence, or violent language.
​Discriminatory jokes, language, or imagery.
​Posting sexually explicit or violent material.
​Plagiarism: Copying content from others without credit is a violation of our core values.
​Sustained disruption of community discussions or "trolling."
​4. Enforcement
​Instances of abusive, harassing, or otherwise unacceptable behavior may be reported to the NJ Blogs project maintainers. The team has the right and responsibility to:
​Remove or edit content that does not align with this Code of Conduct.
​Temporarily or permanently ban users who violate these rules.
​5. Attribution
​This Code of Conduct is adapted from the Contributor Covenant, version 2.1.
